PHP Auth System

Secure login/signup system built with raw PHP, MySQLi (OOP), and Docker.

Features:

- User registration & login
- Password hashing (bcrypt)
- MySQLi prepared statements (SQL injection protection)
- Session management
- Environment variables (.env)
- Dockerized environment

Tech Stack:

- PHP 8.5
- MySQLi (OOP style)
- MySQL 8.0
- Docker & Docker Compose

Project Structure:
├── auth/
│ ├── login.php # Login handler
│ └── signup.php # Signup handler
├── css/
│ ├── login.css
│ ├── main.css
│ ├── profile.css
│ └── signup.css
├── .env # Database credentials (gitignored)
├── config.php # Database class with MySQLi methods
├── docker-compose.yml
├── Dockerfile
├── index.php
├── login.html # Login form
├── signup.html # Signup form
└── profile.php # User dashboard


Run Locally:
  ```bash
  Clone repo
  git clone https://github.com/yourusername/php-mysqli-auth.git
  cd php-auth-system
  # Copy environment config
  cp .env.example .env
  # create .env with :
    Environment Variables:
      DB_HOST=db
      DB_NAME=your_database
      DB_USER=your_username
      DB_PASSWORD=your_password
      DB_ROOT_PASSWORD=your_root_password
  # Start Docker containers
  docker-compose up -d
  # Import database schema
  docker exec -i mysql-container mysql -u root -p your_db < schema.sql
  Access: http://localhost:8080
Security:
  Password hashing with bcrypt.
  MySQLi prepared statements (bind_param).
  Session regeneration on login.
  Environment variables for credentials.
